## Secrets Management

Directory structure and permissions are non-negotiable:
```
config/secrets/         chmod 700
├── db_password         chmod 600  — plain text value
├── llm_api_keys        chmod 600  — JSON {"provider": "key"}
├── discord_token       chmod 600  — plain text value
├── slack_bot_token     chmod 600  — plain text value
└── slack_app_token     chmod 600  — plain text value

config/talon.toml       chmod 600
```

Any script that creates files in `config/secrets/` must:
```bash
chmod 700 config/secrets
chmod 600 config/secrets/*
```

**Never:**
- Put secrets in `.env` (use for `NODE_ENV`, `LOG_LEVEL` only)
- Put secrets in `docker-compose.yml` environment vars
- Put secrets in systemd unit `Environment=` lines
- Commit any file from `config/secrets/` to git

`.gitignore` must include:
```
config/secrets/
config/talon.toml
data/logs/
*.jsonl
```

