## Makefile Targets

All operational commands go through the Makefile. Never give raw commands
to the user when a `make` target exists. Targets to maintain:

```makefile
dev          # Start backend (--reload) + frontend (vite dev) concurrently
build        # npm run build → frontend/dist/
deploy       # build + copy dist + restart talon.service + nginx reload
migrate      # alembic upgrade head
services-up  # docker compose up -d
services-down# docker compose down
health       # curl /api/health | jq
logs         # tail -f data/logs/talon.jsonl | jq
logs-errors  # grep errors from log stream
status       # systemctl status + docker compose ps
```

---

## Deployment Checklist (Run Every Deploy)

```bash
# 1. Run tests first — never deploy a failing test suite
make test

# 2. Build frontend
make build

# 3. Verify config permissions
ls -la config/
ls -la config/secrets/

# 4. Validate config parses correctly
cd backend && python -c "from app.core.config import get_settings; get_settings()"

# 5. Test nginx config
nginx -t

# 6. Deploy
make deploy

# 7. Verify
make health
make status
journalctl -u talon.service -n 50
```

