## Log Management

Logs are JSON lines at `data/logs/talon.jsonl`.

View live: `tail -f data/logs/talon.jsonl | python3 -m json.tool`
View errors only: `grep '"level":"error"' data/logs/talon.jsonl | jq`

Rotation runs daily at 2am via APScheduler. Files > 10 MB are gzip-archived.
Archives: `data/logs/talon-YYYYMMDD.jsonl.gz`

For systemd journal (startup errors before logging initializes):
```bash
journalctl -u talon.service --since "1 hour ago"
```

---

## Resource Monitoring

```bash
# Memory by process
ps aux --sort=-%mem | head -20

# Docker container stats
docker stats --no-stream

# Disk usage
df -h /
du -sh data/logs/ data/memories/

# Open connections
ss -tlnp | grep -E '8000|5432|8080'
```

Alert thresholds (manual checks until monitoring is wired):
- RAM > 12 GB used: investigate
- Disk > 80 GB used: rotate/archive logs
- talon.service restart count > 3 in 1 hour: check logs for crash loop
